  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "*Title*: Internal Redirect: Add support for configurable maximum hops and request with body\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nAdd configurable maximum number of hops internal redirect should follow. The current behavior is that maximum_hops always equals to 1. The state is tracked by existence of x-envoy-original-url. We should do this bookkeeping in StreamInfo::FilterState once #9143 is done.\r\n\r\nNumber of maximum hops can be configured at the HCM level or the route level.\r\n\r\nHCM level is easier to implement.\r\n\r\nroute level is confusing since route can change across redirects, but maybe we can always respect the config on the first route a request hits?",
